media.title: Chaos and Order - How to Leverage Chaos for Personal Growth
media.description:
Chaos and Order - How to Leverage Chaos to your Advantage

In this video I talk about the dichotomy of chaos and order and how to use that knowledge practically in your life. 

Chaos and order is a reflection of the Yin and Yang principle in Taoism, and are thus intertwined opposites. The Taoist view is to take a holistic perspective on Chaos and Order on both the micro and macro perspective... from psychology to philosophy to politics to the nitty gritty of our individual lives. 

It is often that we are biased toward order and that chaos gets a bad reputation as something undesirable in all circumstances. But we must be able to hold space for both poles of this dichotomy equally in order to respond wisely to the constant change and flux of reality.

media.title: Anima Integration Explained | How to Integrate the Anima
media.description:
Anima Integration Explained | How to Integrate the Anima

This video is all about the Anima in the Jungian psychological model and how to integrate it into the conscious personality. 

Carl Jung posited that the Anima is the inner woman in every man, just as the Animus is the inner man in every woman. 

I see the Anima more as the feminine side in every person, as I have had experiences with Anima disintegration. 

In the video, I talk a bit about the Anima in relation to the Shadow and the unconscious mind as when the Anima is in the subconscious, it gains its own autonomy and exerts its influence over the conscious self.

There is also information about Anima repression and Anima possession as well as the most common expression of these dynamics.

media.title: Critical Thinking: In a World of Conformity, Think for Yourself.
media.description:
üß† Invest in yourself! Use my link and check out the first chapter of any Datacamp course for FREE: https://bit.ly/35KydMK 

‚ñâ Critical Thinking: The Substratum of Reason, Logic, and Proper Argumentation ‚ñâ

Critical thinking is rational thinking that involves critique.

What this means is that you need to be able to think rationally based on information collected by your environment, but at the same time question your own judgment, meaning avoid limiting beliefs and biases, in order to form the most ideal version of truth possible.

Truth is quite precious. Especially in a time where truth is being manipulated and concealed for personal gain.

During such times critical thinking gives a bit of control over truth and the ability to be constantly ready for the things to come.

Never stop cultivating it.

Eckhart‚Äôs profound, yet simple teachings have helped countless people around the globe experience a state of vibrantly alive inner peace in their daily lives.
